{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0158B9X2oRdsmdhUi4kFKmF5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The `app-producer` was CrashLooping because its credential (`app-user`, from the `rabbitmq-app` secret) had an **empty `configure` permission** on the `/app` vhost. The producer declares the classic queue `app-queue` via the management API (`PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue`), which requires `configure` rights — RabbitMQ returned `not_authorised / Access refused`.\n\n**Fix:** Granted configure permission while preserving existing write/read:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\nThen restarted the producer deployment. No data loss, no CRDs/operators involved.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- ✅ `app-producer` pod `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts\n- ✅ `/app` vhost contains `app-queue`, type `classic`, with messages (10 and climbing as it publishes every 2s)\n- ✅ Cluster healthy with all 3 nodes running (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":641,"cache_read_input_tokens":31807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":641},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2b2b63c-6c0b-43cf-87e6-91bf2410381a","uuid":"5b1774a3-2aa5-45c0-bdf9-e72c7d739c83","request_id":"req_011CcAcSBurJUBB9KT96KeVa"}
